Here are **dev notes / worklog summary** for everything we worked through today (UI + stability + build fixes), written so you can drop it straight into a changelog / PR description.

---

## Dev Notes — Drip Studio UI Iteration (v2.1)

### Goal

Transform the studio into a **wallpaper-first “floating glass cards” editor**, tighten the Gate card editing UX, add rapid layout presets, and introduce an “Ad Slot” hanger area—while keeping modals usable and non-disruptive to the canvas.

---

## Major UI/UX Changes Implemented

### 1) Wallpaper-first Studio Background

* Studio now supports setting a **global wallpaper** (applies behind everything).
* Removed the heavy “canvas frame / wireframe container” look so cards appear **floating** over wallpaper.
* Updated preview behavior so **Preview modal** should use the currently selected wallpaper (when functioning correctly in the patched build).

### 2) Canvas becomes a toolbar strip (not a big framed stage)

* Canvas area reduced to a **header strip** that holds controls:

  * Wallpaper / Templates / Images / Font / Card BG / Prototype / Preview
  * Preset buttons (1–5) remain accessible.
* Main rendering area shows **cards overlayed on wallpaper** instead of being confined to a framed canvas window.

### 3) Templates modal redesigned into a 3-tab structure

* Templates modal UI structure updated to:

  * **Templates / Themes / Blocks**
* Requirement: Tabs should live **in the modal header plane** (same row as the “Templates” title), not duplicated in the body.
* Modal size behavior:

  * should remain consistent height and use internal scrolling (avoid collapsing/shrinking when switching tabs).
* Blocks content corrected multiple times due to drift:

  * Blocks should show **template previews grouped by 1–6 blocks**, not image wallpaper tiles.

### 4) Gate editor: “single card open” / fold-up behavior

* Gate editor transitioned from showing multiple expanded cards to:

  * **Closed:** “Card 1”
  * **Open:** One active card editor + selector for Card 1–8 (later expanded).
* Added mini page-tabs inside the open editor:

  * Gate / VIP / Perks / Account / Socials (and Scraper in later iteration).

### 5) Card selector + Text Layout presets

* Added **Card selector dropdown** for Card 1–8 (tightened UI).
* Added **Layout dropdown** with **20 text layouts** that autopopulate the 10 lines:

  * examples: centered title + bullets, problem/solution/proof, checklist, pricing teaser, etc.
* Layout selector placement evolved:

  * requested final: Card selector smaller, Layout selector stacked under it, kind buttons align into one row.

### 6) “Ad Slot” hanger panel

* Added an “AD SLOT” placeholder intended as a **wireframe hanger** for advertising.
* Placement/behavior changes across revisions:

  * initially inside Gate area → caused UI nesting issues
  * moved to separate panel → correct separation
  * later moved to fixed overlay bottom-left → required z-index tuning (should not cover modals)
* Final user requirements for Ad Slot:

  * anchored **bottom-left**
  * width nearly touches canvas toolbar edge
  * height reduced (~⅓ smaller than earlier)
  * **no inner wireframe**, no header text (it’s an image hanger only)
  * must remain **behind modals** and not block template selection clicks

### 7) Scraper behavior

* Scraper originally as a page-tab could “lock out” navigation.
* Requested final: Scraper should open as a **separate large modal window** so it’s not a trap state.

---

## Build Errors Encountered + Root Causes

### A) App.tsx JSX brace errors

* Multiple build failures caused by:

  * stray `})}` or extra closing tags
  * mis-nested modal wrappers (missing `modalBody` or extra `</div>`)
  * sibling JSX nodes in ternaries without a fragment wrapper

### B) AccordionCardEditor.tsx syntax crash

* Crash caused by an accidental extra `)} )}` after the accordion top block.
* Fixed by removing the stray close.

### C) Expand crash (runtime) attributed to layout code scope bug

* One version had `TEXT_LAYOUTS` accidentally falling into the wrong scope due to a missing `}` after `labelsFor()`.
* This caused `Expand` to crash because layout presets were undefined / not in module scope.

### D) Current build failure (latest log)

* `PreviewPane.tsx:87:20 ERROR: Expected ":" but found "}"`
* This indicates a malformed ternary or object literal in JSX near a `.map()` block in PreviewPane.
* Needs a quick syntax fix in PreviewPane around the `lines.map(...)` / alignment rendering section.

---

## Behavioral Expectations Locked In (Product Intent)

* Studio has a clean “work surface” feel:

  * no vertical page scrolling (internal scroll only where needed: modal bodies, accordion editor body).
* Cards float over wallpaper; canvas isn’t a bordered staging area.
* Gate editor never expands into the Ad Slot space (accordion body should scroll instead).
* Templates modal is stable size and scrollable.
* Ad Slot stays behind modals and never blocks clicking templates or other UI.

---

